---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Saint Lucia Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/saint-lucia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Barbados for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/barbados' },
  { title: 'Antigua for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/antigua-and-barbuda' },
  { title: 'Grenada for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/grenada' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'stLuciaFit', header: 'St Lucia Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,350-1,930/mo', stLuciaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,580-2,255/mo', stLuciaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,215-1,735/mo', stLuciaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'GeoBlue', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,130-1,615/mo', stLuciaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Sagicor)', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$400-800/mo', stLuciaFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'XCD$1,215-1,930', annual: 'XCD$14,580-23,160' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'XCD$1,665-2,575', annual: 'XCD$19,980-30,900' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'XCD$2,240-3,450', annual: 'XCD$26,880-41,400' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic Visit', monthly: 'XCD$250-500/visit', annual: 'As needed' },
  { category: 'Medical Evacuation', monthly: 'N/A', annual: 'XCD$50,000-150,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Saint Lucia 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors in Saint Lucia. Piton mountains, romantic beaches, citizenship by investment, and coverage for retirees 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Saint Lucia"
  subheadline="Saint Lucia offers iconic Piton mountains, volcanic beaches, luxury resorts, citizenship by investment, and romantic atmosphere—one of the Caribbean's most beautiful destinations for retirement."
  heroImage="/images/countries/saint-lucia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Saint Lucia</h2>
  <p>
    Saint Lucia offers the iconic Pitons (UNESCO World Heritage), dramatic volcanic landscape, luxury resorts, English-speaking environment, and citizenship by investment program. For romantic couples and nature lovers seeking Caribbean beauty, Saint Lucia provides stunning scenery and tropical lifestyle.
  </p>

  <p>
    Castries is the capital with main services. Rodney Bay has best tourist infrastructure. Soufrière near the Pitons is dramatic but remote. Population ~180,000. Miami is 4 hours by flight; Martinique (French hospitals) 30 minutes.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; Martinique/Miami evacuation common</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English; French Creole spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> XCD$6,000-12,000/month (~$2,200-4,400 USD); moderate-high</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; warm year-round; hurricane season</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Romantic; scenic; laid-back</li>
      <li><strong>Tax:</strong> No capital gains tax</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Saint Lucia Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Saint Lucia healthcare is limited—Victoria Hospital (Castries) is main public facility. Tapion Hospital is private option. Limited specialists. Complex cases evacuate to Martinique (30-minute flight, French healthcare) or Miami (4 hours). International insurance with evacuation coverage essential for seniors.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private clinics handle routine care. Dental available. Martinique provides closer backup than Miami with excellent French hospitals (CHU de Fort-de-France). Include both in coverage area.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Martinique Backup Key</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Martinique (French department) has excellent healthcare just 30 minutes away. CHU de Fort-de-France provides French-quality care. Ensure insurance covers Martinique/French territories. Closer and often better than US evacuation for many conditions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Saint Lucia residency options:
  </p>

  <h3>Citizenship by Investment</h3>
  <p>
    $100,000+ donation or $200,000+ real estate. Saint Lucia passport provides visa-free travel to 140+ countries. Growing program.
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residency</h3>
  <p>
    Available after years of residence or through investment. Right to live without working.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Stay</h3>
  <p>
    Visa extensions available. Good for testing retirement before committing.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Saint Lucia:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residency:</strong> International coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Martinique and Miami coverage critical</li>
    <li><strong>Hurricane:</strong> Evacuation consideration important</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Saint Lucia</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Comprehensive international insurance covering Martinique (French territories) and Miami/US. Local care handles routine needs. Martinique often preferred for non-emergencies due to proximity and quality.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Saint Lucia, regional evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Saint Lucia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Americas/Europe network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Martinique access:</strong> Close French healthcare backup</li>
    <li><strong>Miami backup:</strong> US hospitals for complex cases</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Saint Lucia with regional evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Saint Lucia (XCD ~2.7 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Martinique network:</strong> Closer than Miami for many needs</li>
    <li><strong>Routine local:</strong> Private clinics affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Hurricane season:</strong> Plan travel off-island</li>
    <li><strong>No capital gains:</strong> Tax advantage for investors</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Romantic Retirees, Both 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $5,000/month combined. Rodney Bay villa. Beach lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global couple plan with Martinique coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XCD$2,700/month combined (~$1,000). Piton views; regional backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: CBI Investor, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $7,000/month. Citizenship by investment. Global traveler.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global worldwide coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XCD$2,000/month (~$740). Global mobility; premium coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Nature Photographer, 65</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,500/month. Soufrière area. Active lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with Caribbean coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XCD$1,300/month (~$480). Dramatic scenery; essential backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Saint Lucia safer than other Caribbean islands?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Relatively safe—lower crime than Jamaica. Tourist areas (Rodney Bay, Soufrière resorts) very safe. Castries has some urban crime. Normal precautions apply. Safer than regional average.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about hurricane risk?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Moderate—Saint Lucia is south of main hurricane belt, so fewer direct hits than northern islands. Still prepare during June-November. Proper construction important. Less risky than Antigua or Bahamas.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why choose Saint Lucia over Barbados?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        More dramatic scenery (Pitons), more romantic atmosphere, less developed, lower costs. Barbados has better healthcare, more infrastructure. Saint Lucia for beauty; Barbados for practicality.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I use Martinique hospitals easily?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes with insurance—30-minute flight to French healthcare. CHU Fort-de-France is excellent. French spoken (helpful if you speak some). Insurance covering French territories essential. Popular backup option.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Saint Lucia coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Healthcare in Saint Lucia is limited—evacuation coverage essential. Always verify current requirements with Saint Lucia authorities.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
